math, primitive Pythagorean triples

Use Euclid's formula to generate all primitive Pythagorean triples: a = m^2-n^2, b = 2*m*n, c = m^2+n^2, where m > n, m and n coprime and m and n have different parity.
Then all Pythagorean triples can be generated by multiples of primitive Pythagorean triples.

0.043s in uva 106 (8/4017)
MLE in poj 1305 (The memory limit here is smaller, so I implemented another slower code which needs less memory.)
